Some new [to me] skincare I've introduced into my routine ☁️ 

• @kiehlscanada calendula herbal extract toner - I didn't expect to like this one as much as I do. My skin gets irritated with the cold weather and this could possibly be saving it. Love how gentle it is.

• @naturiumskin niacinamide serum 12% plus zinc 2% - My skin really loves this! There's been a noticeable difference in the appearance with this one. My skin's also been a lot clearer since being introduced to it.

• @ustawiskincare niacinamide dark spot corrector - I've been using this only on past acne marks, and although it takes time for those to fade, I do find this has helped over time.

• @charlottetilbury magic serum crystal elixir - I can't believe it took this long for me to try this serum. It doesn't disappoint. I love the way my skin looks and feels after application.

• charlotte tilbury magic cream instant turnaround moisturizer - I see the hype with this moisturizer now! I've been using it in the mornings before I apply makeup and it sits beautifully underneath.

• @cocokind resurrection polypeptide cream - I find this cream too thick for the daytime on my oily skin, but for night it's been a great one. 

• @nuxeca crème fraîche de beauté - There's multiple ways of using this product, but I've been using it only as a hand cream. It does a great job at keeping my hand moisturized this winter.

• @topicals exfoliating body serum - I've been testing this out on my legs and bikini area and so far so good. The product however, dispenses way too much and I can't seem to control it as you can briefly see in my reel, lol.
.
.
.
.

A makeup look using mostly all new products, and sharing my thoughts on them 👇🏼

✨️ @armanibeauty luminous silk foundation in 5.75 - This is actually my second time trying this, and initially I didn't like it. I don't know what changed but this time around I'm loving how my skin looks. It looks like a perfect second skin. 

✨️ @narsissist laguna talc-free bronzer powders in laguna 03 and laguna 02 - I've said it many times, but I'm happy nars had been making talc-free formulas now. I've never tried the laguna bronzers before but really love how smooth and easy they are to blend.

✨️ amani beauty luminous silk glow blush in 60 mystery and 50 euphoric - I fall in love with blushes a lot but I feel these one's really got me in a chokehold. They blend like a dream and this combo together especially looks amazing.

✨️ nars laguna sunset quad (limited edition) - This is definitely a summer eyeshadow palette and I believe it would make all eye colours pop in the sunlight.

✨️ @sacheubeauty lip liner stay-n liner tattoo in p-inked - So this isn't a new one but I feel I should give an update on this since I absolutely love it! It  stays on until I remove it with an oil cleanser.

✨️ @naturiumskin phyto-glow lip balm - This balm is a bit too sticky but I actually don't mind it since I've noticed I don't need to touch up as much and my lips stay hydrated for much longer than usual.

✨️ armani beauty lip power satin long lasting lipstick in 113 elegant and 107 sensual - Although I have a big lipstick collection I'm quite picky about my favourites and I gotta say this comes as a close runner up to the CT ones. They're very comfortable throughout the day and the colours are very flattering.

I went to @fusionmedcc to get my first IPL treatment! I've always been self-conscious about the redness in my skin even though I've had it since I can remember, but it was an amazing opportunity to be able to finally treat it. It was also nice to hear I've been doing well with taking care of my skin from Dr Annie. It's been more than 2 weeks actually since my treatment, and have noticed the redness in my skin has really gone down. Thanks to the team for making me feel more comfortable in my own skin again!

Btw, if you stop by FusionMed and mention me, you'll get 10% off your services!

my thoughts below on the new @kayali oudgasm collection:

Café Oud - I really thought this one would be my fave, but on it's own it doesn't wow with my body chemistry. To solve it, I've found that layering it with Rose Oud creates the perfect balance and gives me a very clean and lightly sweet scent (smells more cafe latte-y together). The combo is my idea of the perfect everyday perfume.

Vanilla Oud - This is the mildest of the ouds. I see this one being a crowd pleaser since it's easy on the nose and is just a well-balanced and very smooth vanilla. I've actually found that layering this with Rose Oud to be my favourite fragrance combo at the moment.

Rose Oud - It takes a lot for me to fall in love with rose note perfumes, but this one stole my heart instantly, so much so that I'm considering buying the full bottle. It's modern yet sensual and sexy. Can't get enough of how beautiful and feminine it is.

Tobacco Oud - This is the strongest one of the bunch. Being the bold fragrance lover that I am, I adore it a lot. I would say two sprays is pushing it, and one is just enough. It's smokey but has a sweetness to it so that it's not totally bitter. This take on tobacco is so well done - probably the best I've ever tried.
